		<td width="150" align="left" valign="top" class="row2"><a name="45240"></a><span class="name"><span class="usercolor">Bellanfear</span></span><img src="templates/subSilver/images/icon_offline.gif" border="0" align="absbottom" alt="Offline" title="Offline" /><div class="gensmall"><img src="images/ranks/rank_7.gif" alt="<b><center><font color=red>Sage</font></b></center>" title="<b><center><font color=red>Sage</font></b></center>" border="0" /><br /><b><center><font color=red>Sage</font></b></center></div><div align="left" class="gensmall">Joined:&nbsp;11 Jan 2004</div><div align="left" class="gensmall">Total posts:&nbsp;843</div><div align="left" class="gensmall">Location:&nbsp;Austin, TX</div><div align="left" class="gensmall">Gender:&nbsp;Male</div></td>
                <td class="row2" width="100%" height="28" valign="top"><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
                        <tr>
                                <td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td><a href="viewtopic.php?p=45240#45240"><img src="templates/subSilver/images/icon_minipost.gif" width="12" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" border="0" /></a><span class="postdetails">Posted: Wed May 26, 2004 12:15 pm<span class="gen">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp; &nbsp;Post subject: </span></td>
                                <td align="right" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><a href="posting.php?mode=quote&amp;p=45240"><img src="templates/subSilver/images/lang_english/icon_quote.gif" alt="Reply with quote" title="Reply with quote" border="0" /></a>    </td></tr></table></td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><hr /></td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Arcady wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Actually, the problem with MoBs regenning on loss of aggro was detrimental to Monks. If a monk was killing a mob and got it to 25 percent health, then FD'd to regen a bit of health, the MoBs would immediately regen to full. It effectively ruined a monks chance at ANY kind of soloing.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">While I see your point here, the problem of Mobs regenning on loss of agro is another example of SOE's consistant failure to solve the root of the problem.  Instead they are constantly treating symptoms.
<br />

<br />
ASSUMPTION:  All experience awarded should be based on effective risk vs reward.
<br />

<br />
ROOT PROBLEM:  Any PoP mob that is killed awards full experience to the people on the agro list, even if they did the nuke, zone, nuke, zone method or if they had a party of higher level people getting the mob to 1% health and membluring it for a lowbie to kill it.
<br />

<br />
SOE's SOLUTION:  Make mobs regen really fast when they lose agro.  This 'solves' the symptoms of the nuke&zone method as well as eliminating some obvious PLing exploits.  However, it really hurts Monks who would like to solo and allows an enchanter to do some lazy healing of their charmed pets.  (I'm sure there's a bard exploit in there as well.)
<br />

<br />
REAL SOLUTION:  Make experience earned from a PoP mob dependant on the health of the mob at the moment the people on the agro list took over the killing.  (OMG!  REAL risk versus reward!!)  
<br />

<br />
For example, random wizard is nuke-zone killing a PoP mob.  The last nuke after zone in takes the mob from 5% health to dead.  The wizard earns 5% of the experience he would earn had he stayed in the zone and solo'd the mob without losing agro.
<br />

<br />
If a monk was low on HP and FD'd to survive, but then started killing agan taking the mob from 25% to dead, then the monk would get 25% of the exp he would have gotten had he not FD'd and been able to kill the mob.
<br />

<br />
Of course, this issue is primarily important for soloers.  There are classes that are better suited to solo than others in this game.  There are so many reasons why this is the case that you can't really solve this issue with a simple experience modifier.  Personally, I dont really care if the soloing 'issue' is fixed or not.  Everyone knows what classes can solo and what ones can't.  If you want to play a class that can do the type of soloing you want, go for it.  As long as SOE doesn't make changes to the game that take away a class's ability to solo, then we are all playing from an even slate in the terms that we should know what we are getting into when we sign up to make that Cleric, Ranger, Monk, etc...  Besides, this is a MMORPG, which means (surprise!) the main idea is to play with other people.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=811231" target="_blank" class="postlink"><img src="http://www.blaynesucks.com/images/Bellanfear.gif" border="0" /></a>
