                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Wybart wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Your proposed change wont stop PL'ing by a higher level character, it only adds one minor step to the process.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">Actually, this is wrong.  It would stop PLing.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Wybart wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Before/now: 1) Highlevel aggroes/pulls mob, 2) Highlevel brings it to 5% (or whatever), 3) Highlevel memblurs/zones, 4) Lowlevel finishes kill for full xp.
<br />
</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">This is accurate as of before they added the PoP mob regen thing a while ago, which is what I'm assuming you meant by process of elimination.  It's not accurate as of the way EQ is now because of PoP mob regen.  Its not accurate as of my initial post since the exp earned would have been 5% and not full.  It's not accurate as of my second post since the exp earned would be 5% and not full exp as well.
<br />

<br />
The way this situation would work in my world is that the Lowbie initiates his fight with the mob at 5% and thus, 5% of the mob's full experience award is the maximum possible exp the Lowbie can earn.  Finishing off a mob at 5% health for 5% of it's possible exp is hardly PLing.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Wybart wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">With change: Add step 1a) Lowlevel casts a low-aggro spell at 97% and enters hate list without aggro. 4b) Lowlevel receives 97% of full xp.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">Now the Lowbie has initiated his fight with the mob at 97% and the maximum possible exp award is 97% of full exp awarded by the mob.  However, according to what I said in my last post here:</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Bellanfear wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Your group initiates the fight on a mob at 100% health and does less than 50% damage to the mob because another group came along and started killing it as well - NO experience to either group.  You could even go so far as to have the mob lootable only by the group who initiated the fight.  This would make loot KSing non-existant, though it would be good to beta test this.  (yeah, right..)</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">He would still have to do more than 50% of the remaining damage to the mob to get ANY exp.
<br />

<br />
It might be important to point out that step three in your scenario is also still necessary for the Lowbie to get any exp.  These rules only work with the highest person on the fight initiated list.  So for example, someone initiates a fight with a 100% healthy mob and bring it to 90%.  If another group started killing at 90% and did a total of 46% of the damage to the mob (i.e. more than half of the remaining health) they would be eligible for a total experience award of 90% only if they were also the highest on the fight initiated list, which could happen if the other people died or zoned.  However, if the other people don't die or zone as they would in step three of your scenario, then they would, as the highest on the fight initiated list get the full exp award since they dealt in total 54% of the mob's health in damage.
<br />

<br />
In terms of PLing, you'd have to be able to do more than half of the damage to the mob to get any exp regardless of your situation.  This means that if you are being PL'd by a damage shield and you can't do more than half of the mob's damage yourself, then you won't get exp.  Also, you would have to be highest on the fight initiated list, so if you are having a highbie pull singles for you, the highbie would have to zone to get off the fight initiated list for you to get exp.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=811231" target="_blank" class="postlink"><img src="http://www.blaynesucks.com/images/Bellanfear.gif" border="0" /></a>
